## ğŸ“– About

**Tau Ä€weko** is a web-based learning platform developed for **Te Whare o Raukura** that teaches students the traditional MÄori numeracy system. The platform features:

- ğŸ“ **Interactive lessons** on base numbers, doubling (pÅ«), and addition (tautahi)
- ğŸ“ **Assessments** with automatic grading and progress tracking
- ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ« **Teacher dashboard** with class management and analytics
- ğŸ“Š **Real-time progress tracking** and detailed student reports
- ğŸŒ **Bilingual interface** (te reo MÄori / English)

---

## âœ¨ Features

### For Students
- **Interactive Learning Path**: 3 progressive lessons covering numbers 1-100
- **Practice Exercises**: Real-time feedback on Tau Ä€weko problems
- **Assessments**: Password-protected evaluations with instant scoring
- **Progress Tracking**: Visual dashboard showing lesson completion and accuracy
- **Class System**: Join classes with unique codes

### For Teachers
- **Class Management**: Create and manage multiple classes with unique codes
- **Student Dashboard**: View all students with color-coded progress badges
- **Analytics**: Comprehensive charts and statistics across all classes
- **Individual Reports**: Deep-dive into each student's performance
- **PDF Export**: Generate bilingual student reports with embedded charts
- **CSV Export**: Download student data for external analysis

---

## ğŸš€ Technology Stack

### Frontend
- **HTML5** - Semantic markup with accessibility features
- **Tailwind CSS** - Utility-first styling via CDN
- **Vanilla JavaScript** - ES6 modules, no framework dependencies
- **Chart.js** - Interactive data visualizations
- **jsPDF + autoTable** - Client-side PDF generation

### Backend
- **Firebase Authentication** - Google OAuth + Email/Password
- **Cloud Firestore** - Real-time NoSQL database
- **GitHub Pages** - Static site hosting

