## ğŸ”§ Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites
- GitHub account
- Firebase account
- Modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)

### Quick Start

1. **Clone this repository:**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/USERNAME/tau-aweko.git
   cd tau-aweko
   ```

2. **Configure Firebase:**
   - Create a Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com
   - Enable Authentication (Email/Password + Google)
   - Create a Firestore database
   - Copy your Firebase config to `firebase-setup.js`

3. **Deploy to GitHub Pages:**
   - Push to GitHub
   - Enable Pages in repository settings
   - Site will be live at: `https://USERNAME.github.io/tau-aweko/`

4. **Configure Firebase domains:**
   - Add `USERNAME.github.io` to Firebase authorized domains

For detailed instructions, see [DEPLOYMENT-CHECKLIST.md](DEPLOYMENT-CHECKLIST.md)

---

## ğŸ¯ Usage

### For Teachers

1. **Create an account:**
   - Visit the site and select "Teacher"
   - Login with Google or email

2. **Create a class:**
   - Navigate to "Manage Classes"
   - Create a new class and copy the class code
   - Share the code with students

3. **Monitor progress:**
   - View all students in the dashboard
   - Check analytics for class performance
   - Generate individual PDF reports

### For Students

1. **Create an account:**
   - Visit the site and select "Student"
   - Login with Google or email
   - Enter your MÄori name when prompted

2. **Join a class:**
   - Enter the class code provided by your teacher

3. **Learn Tau Ä€weko:**
   - Complete 3 progressive lessons
   - Practice with interactive exercises
   - Take the assessment (password required)

